[normal]Riverside is one of the largest housing association groups in the country, owning and managing over 53,000 properties across England and Scotland. The Riverside Group Limited is the main asset-owning association in the group. In addition to providing gener
[normal]al needs accommodation, Riverside delivers supported housing through a sheltered and supported arm of the business, Riverside ECHG (RECHG), which provides services to more than 11,500 
[normal]vulnerable 
[normal]clients with a diverse range of housing needs.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]1.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Riverside
[normal] wel
[normal]comes the opportunity to 
[normal]submit views
[normal] to the
[normal] Work and Pensions Select C
[normal]ommittee 
[normal]as part of
[normal] the inquiry
[normal] 
[normal]into support for housing costs in the 
[normal]r
[normal]eformed welfare system. 
[normal]Our evid
[normal]ence is presented in three sections
[normal]:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]commentary
[normal] on
[normal] the
[normal] early
[normal] operational
[normal] impact of welfare reform for 
[normal]our customers and 
[normal]Riverside as a
[normal] social business
[normal];
[normal]
